                <h1>Discover the Origins of Fendi: Who Created This Iconic Brand?</h1>
                <p>Fendi was founded in 1925 by Edoardo and Adele Fendi in Rome, Italy. Initially a fur and leather shop, it grew into a luxury fashion powerhouse renowned for its innovative designs and craftsmanship. The brand skyrocketed to global fame with the introduction of the 'Baguette' bag and the iconic 'FF' logo, making it a staple in high fashion.</p>
